00:44:56,153 --> 00:44:59,088
[ Thunder Rolling, Lightning Crashing ]

567
00:45:00,825 --> 00:45:03,487
Aaaaaah !

568
00:45:03,561 --> 00:45:05,529
[ Luana ] What happened?

569
00:45:05,596 --> 00:45:09,464
[ Bergen ] When the shadow lifted,
the golden harp was gone.

570
00:45:09,533 --> 00:45:13,333
No longer was the valley happy,
for without the magic of the harp,

571
00:45:13,404 --> 00:45:17,670
all was misery,
misery, misery.

572
00:45:17,742 --> 00:45:19,903
[ Charlie ] Just like the eighth grade.

573
00:45:19,977 --> 00:45:21,945
[ Bergen ] Desolation
spread over the land.

574
00:45:22,012 --> 00:45:24,207
Everything was drying up.

575
00:45:24,281 --> 00:45:26,613
-[ Mortimer ] Dry rot.
-[ Charlie ] Yes, isn't it ?

576
00:45:26,684 --> 00:45:28,618
-[ Bergen ] Charlie.
-[ Charlie ] Yes, sir.

577
00:45:28,686 --> 00:45:32,178
[ Bergen ] The fields of golden corn
turned to dust.

578
00:45:32,256 --> 00:45:34,190
[ Charlie ] Kerplop.

579
00:45:34,258 --> 00:45:37,250
[ Bergen ] The laughing brook
flowed no more.

580
00:45:40,998 --> 00:45:44,559
To think that this
was once Happy Valley!

581
00:45:44,635 --> 00:45:46,569
[ Charlie ] Now it's Gruesome Gulch.

582
00:45:46,637 --> 00:45:49,606
[ Bergen ] Days pass, weeks pass.

583
00:45:49,673 --> 00:45:52,369
[ Charlie ] I pass. New deal.

584
00:45:52,443 --> 00:45:55,173
[ Luana ] What happened
to all the people ?

585
00:45:55,246 --> 00:45:57,646
[ Bergen ] Well, suppose we look in
on these humble peasants.

586
00:45:57,715 --> 00:46:00,980
-[ Mortimer ] Is that a peasant ?
-[ Charlie ] That's a cow, stupid.

587
00:46:01,051 --> 00:46:03,178
[ Luana ] Well, at least they had milk.

588
00:46:03,254 --> 00:46:05,779
[ Bergen ] Well, she used to be
a good milker. But now--

589
00:46:05,856 --> 00:46:08,689
[ Charlie ] She's an udder failure.

590
00:46:08,759 --> 00:46:12,320
[ Bergen ] She was the bosom friend
of a once-proud family.

591
00:46:12,396 --> 00:46:14,887
[ Charlie ] Well, they're certainly
out of the high rent district.

592
00:46:14,965 --> 00:46:16,830
[ Hinge Squeaking ]

593
00:46:16,901 --> 00:46:18,835
[ Bergen ] And there they are,

594
00:46:18,903 --> 00:46:24,000
three poor farmers, gripped
by the pangs of starvation.

595
00:46:24,074 --> 00:46:26,668
Still alive, still breathing,

596
00:46:26,744 --> 00:46:29,338
sharing a pitiful crust
between them.

597
00:46:29,413 --> 00:46:32,678
Share and share alike.

598
00:46:32,750 --> 00:46:37,016
Sharing and staring.
Staring and sharing.

599
00:46:37,087 --> 00:46:39,351
[ Charlie ] Uh,just tell it,
don't ham it.

600
00:46:39,423 --> 00:46:41,721
[ Bergen ] But are
their spirits broken ?

601
00:46:41,792 --> 00:46:43,783
Have they lost hope ?

602
00:46:43,861 --> 00:46:48,696
Yes. Men facing famine,
naught left but beans.

603
00:46:48,766 --> 00:46:51,963
[ Charlie ] Ahem. Bean,you mean.

604
00:46:52,036 --> 00:46:54,732
[ Bergen ] If it were one man
and three beans--

605
00:46:54,805 --> 00:46:59,003
But, no. One bean
and three men.

606
00:46:59,076 --> 00:47:01,977
[ Charlie ] Well, at least
there are no bones in it.

607
00:47:02,112 --> 00:47:04,478
[ Bergen ] Just look at that
miserable creature,

608
00:47:04,548 --> 00:47:07,244
doggedly struggling
to maintain life,

609
00:47:07,318 --> 00:47:10,947
a gaunt, lean bag
of bones and feathers.

610
00:47:11,021 --> 00:47:14,286
Truly a picture
of despair.

611
00:47:14,358 --> 00:47:17,555
But Donald
doesn't whimper.

612
00:47:17,628 --> 00:47:20,620
- Donald doesn't give up.
- Shut up !

613
00:47:20,698 --> 00:47:23,166
I can't stand it !
[ Squawking ]

614
00:47:25,736 --> 00:47:27,670
[ Mickey Shouting ]

615
00:47:27,738 --> 00:47:30,798
[ Goofy ] Easy, Donald. Easy!

616
00:47:30,875 --> 00:47:34,276
[ All Shouting At Once ]

617
00:47:34,345 --> 00:47:37,143
There. There, now.
There. Easy, Donald.

618
00:47:37,214 --> 00:47:39,580
I-- I'll be all right.

619
00:47:39,650 --> 00:47:42,448
Yeah. I'll be all right.
[ Panting ]

620
00:47:42,519 --> 00:47:44,578
I'll be all right.

621
00:47:51,161 --> 00:47:53,959
[ Bergen ] He says he's all right,
but I wonder.

622
00:47:54,031 --> 00:47:56,431
He's suffered too much.

623
00:47:56,500 --> 00:47:59,799
What diabolical thought
is being hatched in the fevered brain...

624
00:47:59,870 --> 00:48:02,430
of this poor, demented duck ?

625
00:48:04,842 --> 00:48:07,436
Donald !
No ! No !

626
00:48:09,513 --> 00:48:11,981
Nice bossy, bossy.

627
00:48:12,049 --> 00:48:14,244
[ Laughs ]

628
00:48:14,318 --> 00:48:17,913
- Nice old cowsy wowsy.
- Donald !

629
00:48:17,988 --> 00:48:20,980
- [ Squawking ]
- [ Mooing ]

630
00:48:21,058 --> 00:48:24,289
- [ Mickey ] Donald! No, Donald!
- [ Mooing ]

631
00:48:24,361 --> 00:48:29,230
[ Squawking ]
Give it here ! Let me--

632
00:48:29,300 --> 00:48:31,234
[ Donald Choking ]

633
00:48:31,302 --> 00:48:35,796
[ Muttering, Panting ]
I just gotta eat.

634
00:48:35,873 --> 00:48:37,807
I'm so... hungry.

635
00:48:37,875 --> 00:48:39,900
[ Bergen ] The little fellow
was completely out of his head.

636
00:48:39,977 --> 00:48:42,411
-Cut it out, will ya ? I get the idea !
-He was a pitiful sight.

637
00:48:42,479 --> 00:48:45,004
- Weeks without food.
- [ Choking, Moaning ]

638
00:48:45,082 --> 00:48:47,312
- Poor Donald.
- Yeah, poor me !

639
00:48:47,384 --> 00:48:49,545
It was all they could
do to restrain him.

640
00:48:49,620 --> 00:48:52,487
- You see, he had just about reached
the end of his rope.
- Yeah.

641
00:48:52,556 --> 00:48:55,389
Oh, it was a sorry
predicament indeed.

642
00:48:55,459 --> 00:48:57,950
What to do ?
What to do ?

643
00:48:58,028 --> 00:49:01,293
Well, Donald may be nuts,
but he's got the right idea.

644
00:49:01,365 --> 00:49:05,859
- Kill the cow.
- Oh, no, Charlie !
The cow was their best friend.

645
00:49:05,936 --> 00:49:09,428
Well, a friend in need
is a friend indeed.

646
00:49:09,506 --> 00:49:12,031
- So what ?
- So, they need some steak.

647
00:49:12,109 --> 00:49:15,078
No ! If you're
gonna kill the cow,

648
00:49:15,145 --> 00:49:18,410
I don't wanna hear
the rest of the story.

649
00:49:18,482 --> 00:49:20,575
Well, she wouldn't
have to know.

650
00:49:20,651 --> 00:49:22,585
They could sneak up on her
and surprise her.

651
00:49:22,653 --> 00:49:26,248
- Yeah, that's what we'll do.
We'll kill the cow.
- Oh, no, Charlie. You mustn't.

652
00:49:26,323 --> 00:49:28,723
We'll get a stranglehold
on her while she's asleep.

653
00:49:28,792 --> 00:49:33,354
- a-a-and then push her off the cliff.
- Oh, no !

654
00:49:33,430 --> 00:49:35,830
I ain't a-gonna listen
to the story.

655
00:49:35,899 --> 00:49:39,027
[ Charlie ] Well, it'll be your fault
if they starve to death.

656
00:49:39,103 --> 00:49:42,197
- [ Luana ]
Why don't they sell the cow?
- That's just what they did.

657
00:49:42,272 --> 00:49:45,708
Well, why didn't you say so in the first
place, and save a lot of time ?

658
00:49:45,776 --> 00:49:49,143
I could save a lot of time by not
telling the story at all !

659
00:49:49,213 --> 00:49:52,148
Your idea is not
without merit.

660
00:49:53,617 --> 00:49:55,551
Well, back to the scene
of desolation.

661
00:49:55,619 --> 00:49:57,712
Things are beginning
to look much brighter now,

662
00:49:57,788 --> 00:50:01,815
because as Mickey goes
to the village to sell the cow,
the thought of prosperity...

663
00:50:01,892 --> 00:50:04,690
